# Git Phase Branch — Procedure

**One session = one PR.** Faz implementation never commits directly to `main`. Each chat aligns with one roadmap iteration and loads the matching phase `.mdc`.

Workflow source: `docs/09_DEV_WORKFLOW.md` Bölüm 5–6, `docs/10_IMPLEMENTATION_ROADMAP.md` Bölüm 1, 8–9.

## Step 0: Preconditions

- [ ] Target faz and iteration identified in `docs/10_IMPLEMENTATION_ROADMAP.md` Bölüm 8 (oturum tablosu).
- [ ] Phase rule exists: `.cursor/rules/5x-phase-*.mdc` (if missing → invoke `@phase-creator` skill first).
- [ ] Prior faz dependencies merged (see Bölüm 2 dependency graph).
- [ ] `main` pulled and CI green.

```
Faz 1 → Faz 2, Faz 3 (parallel OK)
Faz 2 + Faz 3 → Faz 4
Faz 4 + öncekiler → Faz 5
```

## Step 1: Load Context (Chat Start)

Agent message format:

```
Faz N — İterasyon M: <short title>
```

Load documents per roadmap oturum table (`docs/10` Bölüm 8):

| Example | Docs |
| --- | --- |
| 1.3 Auth backend | `03` auth §, `07`, `08` |
| 2.2 Campaign backend | `03` campaigns §, `07` |
| 4.1 WebSocket gateway | `04` §9, `03` §14 |
| 4.2 DM Screen FE | `06` Grup 3, `05` §8 |

Invoke phase rule:

```
@50-phase-01-...mdc   (exact filename from .cursor/rules/)
```

Phase `.mdc` contains iteration blueprint — follow its file list and Done criteria without re-planning.

## Step 2: Create Feature Branch

From updated `main`:

```bash
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b <type>/<short-description>
```

Branch naming (`docs/09` Bölüm 5):

```
feat/campaign-invite-regeneration
feat/auth-refresh-rotation
fix/ws-join-campaign-forbidden
test/character-ownership-matrix
chore/ci-prisma-migrate-deploy
```

Align name with iteration scope — one logical deliverable.

**Forbidden:** work on `main`, force-push `main`.

## Step 3: Implement Iteration Scope

Respect phase `.mdc` grain:

```
[ ] ≤12 files per chat/PR (phase-creator guideline)
[ ] Only iteration M deliverables — no "while here" faz N+1 work
[ ] Use how-tos: @40 endpoint, @41 screen, @42 migration, @43 policy, @47 WS
[ ] MVP out-of-scope items not added (00-project-identity)
```

Human gates (`docs/10` Bölüm 9):

- Agent does **not** merge to `main` without user approval.
- Agent does **not** advance faz without human faz sign-off.

## Step 4: Conventional Commits

```
<type>(<scope>): <description>

feat(campaigns): add invite link regeneration endpoint
test(characters): add ownership guard integration tests
fix(websocket): reject join-campaign for non-members
```

Types: `feat` | `fix` | `chore` | `refactor` | `test` | `docs`

Scopes: `auth`, `campaigns`, `characters`, `homebrew`, `web`, `shared`, `ci`, `db`, `websocket`, etc.

## Step 5: Pre-PR Local Gates

```bash
docker compose up -d
pnpm lint
pnpm typecheck
pnpm test
pnpm --filter web build && pnpm --filter api build
```

If migration in PR:

```bash
pnpm --filter api prisma migrate dev   # local only
pnpm --filter api prisma db seed
```

Checklist (`docs/09` Bölüm 6):

```
[ ] Conventional commit messages
[ ] Auth matrix tests if policy touched
[ ] .env.example updated if new env var
[ ] Seed works after migration
[ ] UI strings English
[ ] No // TODO: mimari karar — unless tracked open decision
```

## Step 6: Push and Open PR

```bash
git push -u origin HEAD
gh pr create --title "feat(campaigns): add invite link regeneration" --body "..."
```

PR title = squash merge commit (Conventional Commits).

PR body template (`docs/09` Bölüm 6):

```markdown
## Context
Faz 2 — İterasyon 2.2: Campaign backend (CRUD + invite + membership)

## Ne değişti?
…

## Neden?
…

## Nasıl test edildi?
- [ ] Unit tests …
- [ ] Integration tests …
- [ ] Manual …

## Kontrol listesi
- [ ] lint / typecheck / test green
- [ ] docs/03 updated if API changed
- [ ] Phase rule Done criteria met
```

## Step 7: CI and Review

Required checks (`docs/09` Bölüm 7):

| Job | Command |
| --- | --- |
| lint | `pnpm lint` + tsc |
| test-backend | `pnpm --filter api test --ci` |
| test-frontend | `pnpm --filter web test --ci` |
| security | `pnpm audit --audit-level=critical` |
| build | web + api build |

Fix failures via `@46-fix-failing-test`. User merges when green + reviewed.

## Step 8: After Merge — Next Iteration

1. Checkout `main`, pull.
2. Confirm iteration M Done in phase `.mdc`.
3. Start **new branch** for iteration M+1.
4. New chat: `Faz N — İterasyon M+1: …`

Do not stack unrelated iterations on one branch.

## Step 9: Faz Completion (Human Gate)

At faz end (`docs/10` Bölüm 9):

| Control | Verify |
| --- | --- |
| CI green | GitHub Actions |
| Auth matrix complete | `docs/08` Bölüm 5 for faz resources |
| Seed works | `docker compose down -v` → full reset |
| UI functional | manual human test |
| No open TODO karar | code scan |

Agent **stops** and waits for human faz approval before planning next faz.

## Step 10: Phase Rule Missing?

If `50+-phase-*.mdc` does not exist for faz N:

1. Stop implementation.
2. Run **`@phase-creator`** skill (not rules-architect).
3. phase-creator updates `docs/10` if needed → writes phase `.mdc`.
4. Resume with Step 1.

rules-architect does **not** write phase `.mdc` files.

## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Multiple faz iterations in one PR
- ❌ Direct push to `main`
- ❌ Starting code without phase `.mdc` or roadmap iteration ID
- ❌ Skipping integration tests "will add in next iteration"
- ❌ Merging without user approval
- ❌ Production deploy from agent (Faz 5 — human only)

## Oturum ↔ Branch Örnekleri

| Chat opener | Branch örneği |
| --- | --- |
| Faz 1 — İterasyon 1.3: Auth backend | `feat/auth-register-login-refresh` |
| Faz 2 — İterasyon 2.2: Campaign CRUD | `feat/campaign-crud-invite` |
| Faz 4 — İterasyon 4.1: WebSocket gateway | `feat/websocket-gateway-redis` |
| Faz 4 — İterasyon 4.6: WS tests | `test/websocket-join-campaign-matrix` |

## Docs vs Phase Rule

| Source | Holds |
| --- | --- |
| `docs/10` Bölüm 8 | Oturum tablosu, yüklenecek doc listesi |
| `50+-phase-*.mdc` | Iterasyon blueprint, dosya listesi, Done |
| How-to 40–47 | Teknik prosedür detayı |

Phase rule wins for iteration scope; docs win on spec conflict.

## Parallel Faz 2 / Faz 3

Branches from same `main` tip OK if teams coordinate — merge conflicts resolved at PR time. Do not mix Faz 2 and Faz 3 work in **one** branch.

## Agent Yasakları (Özet)

From `01-coding-philosophy.mdc` + roadmap §1:

- `main`'e push yok
- Production deploy yok
- Faz geçişi onayı yok
- Açık karar varsayımı yok

## Implementasyon Sonrası

When faz iteration merged, optional **`@phase-controller`** skill:

- Gap audit kod vs docs
- `Docs/fix-reports/` output
- Does not replace human faz gate

## Troubleshooting

| Issue | Resolution |
| --- | --- |
| Phase .mdc missing | `@phase-creator` — not rules-architect |
| PR too large | Split per iteration; use `@split-to-prs` if needed |
| CI red on main after merge | New branch `fix/ci-...` from main |
| Dependency not merged | Wait for prerequisite faz PR |

